        jTextPane1.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Arial", 0, 18)); // NOI18N
        jTextPane1.setText("1. Pangong Lake\nThis lake covers a total area of 600 square kilometers and some parts of this lake are in China and Tibet as well and is one of the best places to visit in Ladakh in summer. The lake remains frozen during the winter months; hence, the warm month of June is the prime time to visit the lake. The lake begins to melt in April and in June it becomes perfect. It’s a saline water body with very less aquatic life in it. A few crustacean species are thriving inside the lake. You will find thousands of exotic birds hovering around the lake and that view is just majestic. You may also opt for camping beside the lake for an exquisite experience. If you visit the lake during summer in June you would also be able to see some rare species of Brahmin ducks and bar-headed goose.\nTimings: Anytime (daytime is better)\nEntry Fees: Free\n\n2. Magnetic Hill\nThis is also called the Gravity Hill as this region is claimed to have magnetic properties. The magnetism is so potent that it can pull the vehicles uphill. People believe that there are natural and supernatural forces that cause magnetic attractions which also makes it one of the distinct places to visit in Ladakh in summer This hill is at an elevation of 14,000 feet above sea level and the layout of the surrounding land creates an optical illusion that shows the downhill slope as an uphill slope. Thus the vehicles seem to be moving uphill even in neutral gear. This interesting place should be a must-visit during June as the weather is pleasant and you get to explore the vicinity and quench your thirst for enthusiasm.\nTimings: 8.00AM – 5.00PM\nEntry Fees: Free\n\n3. Thiksey Monastery\nThis Tibetan Buddhist Monastery is located at an altitude of 3,600 meters and is also called the Thikse Gompa. This 12-storey beautiful building has many items that resemble Buddhism and is one of the spiritual places to visit in Ladakh in summer It is placed when you can find peace and get acquainted with the Buddhist ethnicity. There are primitive scriptures, paintings, statues and swords that are worth seeing. This monastery is one of the popular monasteries in Ladakh which attracts many tourists every year. June is the pleasurable month to explore the enchanting beauty of the monastery as the weather is soothing and you do not feel tired. Inside the complex of the monastery, you can stop by the Tara Temple and check out the 21 images dedicated to goddess Tara which is quite attractive.\nTimings: 6.00AM – 1.00PM and 1.30AM – 6.00PM\nEntry Fees: INR 20/-\n\n4. Royal Leh Palace\nThis is a former palace of the royal family of Leh and is also known as Lichen Palkhar. Built-in the 17th century, this 9 storey building was one of the tallest structures of its time and is one of the places to visit in Ladakh in summer that you can’t miss. Today, this palace has become a favorite tourist spot as the views of the Ladakh mountain ranges and Stok Kangri from here are simply awe-inspiring. This palace is an important destination of the Buddhist religion and culture. In recent times, the palace has deteriorated to a run-down condition and is being restored by the Archaeological Survey of India. As there are many things to prospect inside the palace, the pleasant weather of June would be the best companion. The Museum of the Palace showcases a rich collection of jewelry, crowns, ornaments and ceremonial dresses.\nTimings: 07.00AM – 04.00PM everyday\nEntry Fees: INR 15/-\n\n5. Indus River\nYou can do many exciting adventures in the heart of the Indus River. Activities like rafting and kayaking are often conducted especially during June, and it continues until August, basically the summer season. This river originates from Pakistan and flows through the parts of Northern India and offers some breathtaking rapids to enhance the spark of the water ventures making it one of the best places to visit in Ladakh in summer. While enjoying the rafting expedition on this river, you would also get to witness the mesmerizing views along the banks of the river. Water sports are best played in the warm months when the temperature of the water is just apt. Hence, if you are in Ladakh in June, get engaged in the jobs by the riverside.\nTimings: Anytime\nEntry Fees: Free\n\n6. Tso Moriri\nThis oligotrophic water body is amongst the high altitude lakes of Ladakh and one of the most famous places to visit in Ladakh in summer. The prime time to visit this lake is during summer. That is because you would get to see many rare species of birds like the bar-headed geese and black-necked cranes. There are numerous camps found around the lake which attract the tourist crowd. Enjoying the cool breeze in the warm month is yet another pleasing moment that you can enjoy during your trip to Ladakh. There is a forest near the lake which is home to many native wild animals like the Himalayan blue sheep, marmot, and Tibetan gazelle. There are chances to spot a snow leopard and Tibetan wolves if you take a troll into the deep jungle.\nTimings: Anytime\nEntry Fees: Free");
